He had a 70-yard touchdown reception from Nick Gauthier in the Red-White Spring Game., 34944=Rushing: 2010/8-16-2.0-0, 33054=2011, 29858=2012: Made one start in the 2012 season against Montana State (10/13/12) when the Eagles began the game with four receivers. He caught two passes for 29 yards versus Montana (9/29/12), and had a 44-yard touchdown in the FCS Playoffs against Illinois State (12/8/12)., 30975=HS: Graduated from Valley Christian HS in 2009. Earned second team all-league honors as he helped lead his team to a 10-3 record in 2008, a 7-3-1 mark in 2007 and 3-7 record in 2006. He had just 68 yards and one touchdown as a senior, but rushed 97 times for 718 yards (7.4 per carry) as a junior with seven touchdowns. He rushed 55 times for 401 yards (7.3 per carry) and six touchdowns in his sophomore season.
